  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In the study conducted by Ventayen [52], the similarity index of ChatGPT-generated results was checked using Turnitin in Philippines.",
    "The results indicated that ChatGPT can generate articles without plagiarism, with similarity ranging from 0 to 10 percent that met the institution's required similarity index.",
    "Basic et al. [5] also revealed that the available ChatGPT text detector may not perform well to detect students work which were written in Croatian language.",
    "These raise the concern about a violation of academic integrity in the university around the world [33,43].Phase two is defined as the remediation period after the CUHK student got caught using ChatGPT for a course assignment.",
    "This incident raised a red flag across the higher education settings in Hong Kong, it also forced CUHK to take prompt action by releasing the AI tools user guideline for students, explicitly stating the penalties for using AI tools without permission and enhancing plagiarism detection software to detect AI-generated work."
  ],
